@startuml
title Inventory/ProductType Release Workflow (Current Reality)

start
:Update code and docs in repo;
:Run local verification as needed;
note right
Available local entrypoints:
- python3 build.py docs
- python3 build.py smoke
- python3 build.py smoke-gui
- scripts/vscode/run_task.sh docs
end note

:Push or merge branch;
:Jenkins pipeline starts;
:Checkout;
:Clean build folder;
:Conan install;
:Canonical docs build (links + optional PlantUML + Doxygen);
:CMake configure;
:CMake build;
:CTest;
:Inventory smoke script;
:GUI startup smoke script;

if (Pipeline green?) then (yes)
    :Archive client binary, server binary,\nbootstrap SQL, and deployment runbook;
    :Manual release review;
    note right
Current gaps in automated release flow:
- PlantUML render still depends on Docker
- archived outputs are not a packaged installer/bundle
- no installer/publish/deploy stage
end note
    :Manual deploy/package decision;
else (no)
    :Fix failures and retry;
endif

stop

